Questions:
Which of the following is considered an experimental procedure in the "Forgotten Voices" study?
A) Completing standard medical treatments for brain cancer; 
B) Participating in the Managing Cancer and Living Meaningfully (CALM) therapy sessions;
C) Attending regular appointments with your primary care physician;
D) Receiving routine care from the hospital's oncology department.

Correct answer: B

If you have any questions or concerns about your participation in the "Forgotten Voices" study, whom should you contact?

A) The American Psychological Foundation;
B) The principal investigator, Dr. Ashlee Loughan, or Kelcie D. Willis, MS;
C) The Department of Health and Human Services;
D) The Virginia Commonwealth University Office of Research.

Correct answer: B) The principal investigator, Dr. Ashlee Loughan, or Kelcie D. Willis, MS.
